article.headline: North Texas 85, Texas St. 62
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- George Odufuwa had 20 points, eight rebounds and five assists to lead North Texas to an 85-62 victory over Texas State on Sunday. Josh White added 18 points for the Mean Green (9-2), who won their 12th straight game at home. North Texas scored the first nine points of the game and built the first-half lead to 32-14 before holding a 40-25 edge at halftime. The margin was 26 points late in the second half. Odufuwa, who was 9 for 12 from the field, tied his career highs in points and assists. The Mean Green made 53.6 percent of their shots while holding the Bobcats to 32.8 percent from the field. Cameron Johnson led Texas State (2-9) with 22 points and seven rebounds.
